# Python Port Plan — Step 00_config

## Goal

Port `week1_baseline/ruby/00_config` (the `Boukensha::Config` + `Boukensha::Tasks`
layer) to Python at `week1_baseline/python/00_config`, as a **literal
architectural mirror** — same classes, same method names/behavior, same
resolution order — not a from-scratch Pythonic redesign. Ruby stays live;
this is an addition, not a replacement (see Decisions below).

This is the first of what will be a repeating pattern as week1_baseline grows
(01_..., 02_..., etc. — a MUD connection layer, the agent loop, tool-calling,
memory). Treat this plan/directory as the template for how future steps get
ported: one `docs/plans/python_port/<step>` file per step, written before
that step's Python code.

## Decisions (confirmed with the user 2026-07-20)

| Question | Decision |
|---|---|
| Port fidelity | **Literal mirror** of the Ruby architecture (Config class, abstract Base task class, Player subclass) — not an idiomatic-Python rewrite |
| Ruby vs Python | **Run alongside** each other, matching the `explore_architecture` pattern of comparing approaches side by side. `week1_baseline/ruby/00_config` is untouched. |
| Tooling | **`uv`** + `pyproject.toml`, matching the existing precedent in `week0_explore/circlemud-world-parser` (`uv` 0.11.29 already installed on this machine) |
| Testing | **Smoke test only** for now — port `examples/example.rb` to `examples/example.py`, same as the Ruby step currently has. No formal `pytest` suite yet (revisit once there's real logic worth unit-testing, e.g. once the agent loop lands). |

