## Target directory layout

```
week1_baseline/python/00_config/
  pyproject.toml          # [project] deps: python-dotenv, pyyaml
  uv.lock                 # committed, matches circlemud-world-parser convention
  .python-version         # "3.14", matches circlemud-world-parser
  README.md                # ported from the Ruby README (schema/resolution-order docs)
  boukensha/
    __init__.py            # mirrors lib/boukensha.rb's aggregating require
    config.py               # Boukensha::Config -> Config
    tasks/
      __init__.py
      base.py                # Boukensha::Tasks::Base -> Base
      player.py               # Boukensha::Tasks::Player -> Player
  prompts/
    system.md                # copied as-is from the Ruby prompts/system.md
  examples/
    example.py                # ported from examples/example.rb
```

Deliberate deviation from the Ruby layout: **no `lib/` wrapper directory.**
Ruby needs `lib/` because `require_relative` has no package-root concept;
Python's packaging tooling (the `boukensha/` directory next to
`pyproject.toml`) already provides that separation, so adding a redundant
`lib/` would fight the tooling for no benefit. Everything *inside*
`boukensha/` mirrors the Ruby `lib/boukensha/` tree 1:1.

