## Decisions (round 2, confirmed with the user 2026-07-20)

| Question | Decision |
|---|---|
| Launcher naming | **`bin/00_config_python`** |
| `requirements.txt` export | **Skip it** — `uv.lock` alone is sufficient, no pip-only consumers to support yet |
| `prompts/system.md` sharing | **Independent copy** per language — simpler, no cross-tree coupling. Accept the small risk of drift; revisit if it actually causes a problem. |
| `uv.lock` commit policy | **Commit it**, matching `circlemud-world-parser`. (Deliberately opposite to the `Gemfile.lock` call on the Ruby side — confirmed intentional, not an oversight: `uv.lock`/`circlemud-world-parser` is the established precedent in *this* repo for Python, whereas the Ruby gem-library convention doesn't have an equivalent local precedent pulling the other way.) |

